article.headline: Valparaiso 56, UMKC 52, OT
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Urule Igbavboa and Calum MacLeod scored seven of Valparaiso's eight points in overtime to lead the Crusaders to an 56-52 win over Missouri-Kansas City on Thursday night. The two led the Crusaders (10-10, 4-2) with 16 points each. MacLeod, a 7-foot-1 junior, hit a 3-pointer 14 seconds into overtime, and Igbavboa had a rebound basket and a dunk in the extra five-minute period. Igbavboa also had a game-high 14 rebounds. UMKC, which lost its fourth straight game, led only briefly at the start of the second half. The Kangaroos (7-15, 2-4) tied the game on a inside basket by Dee Ayuba with 24 seconds left in regulation. Ayuba and Quinton Day led the Kangaroos with 17 points each. The Crusaders, who won their fourth straight game, led 27-22 at halftime. UMKC didn't score its first field goal until nearly 12 minutes had gone by in the first half. The Kangaroos were just 6-of-21 from the field in the first half, and finished the game hitting 17-of-52 shots, or 33 percent. Valparaiso didn't fare much better from the floor, hitting 20-of-55 attempts, or 36 percent.
